Two Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC) officers in Anambra State have been reportedly shot dead on Ezinifite-Uga Road in Aguata Local Government Area of the state. An eyewitness said the two officers were killed by yet to be identified persons in the area. According to the eyewitness, “Please avoid Igbo Ukwu-Ezinifite-Uga Rd now. Two road safety officials were shot dead between Ezinifite and Uga at about 2 pm today Sunday, April 3.” The Anambra FRSC Sector is yet to respond to the enquiry sent to it. More details soon… 